docs.abstract: Earnings at Saudi Arabia’s giant oil company, at $111 billion last year, far outstripped the profits of giant tech companies or rival oil producers.
docs.snippet: Earnings at Saudi Arabia’s giant oil company, at $111 billion last year, far outstripped the profits of giant tech companies or rival oil producers.
docs.lead_paragraph: The earnings of Saudi Arabia’s giant oil company have long been a mystery, kept under wraps by the country’s government. But on Monday, Saudi Aramco opened its books, revealing that it generated $111.1 billion in net income last year, making it probably the world’s most profitable company by far.

headline.main: Saudi Aramco Is World’s Most Profitable Company, Beating Apple by Far
headline.print_headline: Profits That Make Even Apple’s Seem Puny
